WEBVTT

00:04.125 --> 00:06.208
-Come on Sheila, Hurry up.
-What's the point?

00:06.250 --> 00:08.417
I'm never going to need
to know this in real life.

00:08.458 --> 00:11.750
-Never gonna...Okay. Alright.

00:13.834 --> 00:15.875
[Gerry]: Okay.

00:15.917 --> 00:18.083
Why don't you tell me what's
really going on here.

00:18.125 --> 00:20.417
What's this really about?
-I'm just not good at this okay?

00:20.458 --> 00:22.834
-No, it's not okay. You can't
be good at everything

00:22.875 --> 00:25.041
I'm going to help you
get good at this.

00:25.083 --> 00:27.375
That's why you come to school.
To learn. That's why we teach.

00:27.417 --> 00:30.250
That's why I did all this
university, to help people.

00:30.291 --> 00:33.333
So don't give up, okay?
You can do this.

00:33.375 --> 00:36.291
We can do this.
Take your time.

00:36.333 --> 00:39.333
Okay? Whaddya got?
Take a look.

00:39.375 --> 00:41.250
You can do it.
-Tyler Toffli.

00:41.291 --> 00:44.125
-Tyler Toffoli.
That's not doing your best.

00:44.166 --> 00:47.208
Look at the rules, please.
You have your forwards.

00:47.250 --> 00:49.667
You need a defence man. How many
times do I have to tell you?

00:49.709 --> 00:52.250
Pick a defence man and hurry up.
We don't have all day.

00:52.291 --> 00:56.291
-Stephanie Robidas.
-Stéphane Robidas.

00:56.333 --> 00:59.000
Okay? There will not be a girl,
ever, in the NHL.

00:59.041 --> 01:01.625
Oh, Hayley Wickenheiser did
it for like, what, a practice?

01:01.667 --> 01:03.875
She didn't play in the game.

01:03.917 --> 01:07.041
Marketing, just a marketing
thing.
[Music]

01:07.083 --> 01:09.250
♪ I'm awesome, no you're not
dude, don't lie ♪

01:09.291 --> 01:12.125
♪ I'm awesome, I'm driving
around in my mom's ride ♪

01:12.166 --> 01:16.083
♪ I'm awesome, a quarter of my
life gone by ♪

01:16.125 --> 01:18.291
♪ I'm awesome ♪

01:20.375 --> 01:22.625
-What's up?

01:22.667 --> 01:25.959
[Gerry sighs]
Hey! What?

01:27.291 --> 01:30.625
Does that say Donovan...
Donovan Bailey?

01:30.667 --> 01:32.917
-Yup.
-What does it say?

01:34.917 --> 01:37.083
-He's in town Friday to raise
some money for something.

01:37.125 --> 01:40.333
-Coming back to my town,
after what that jerk did to me.

01:40.375 --> 01:43.083
Huh. What that jerk did to me.

01:44.333 --> 01:46.291
-[Bill takes a deep breath]

01:46.333 --> 01:48.458
-You don't want to know
what that jerk did to me?

01:48.500 --> 01:50.709
-No, I don't Gerry, I'm tired of
it.

01:50.750 --> 01:52.875
'Cause it's always something
with you. Lemme guess.

01:52.917 --> 01:55.500
Donovan Bailey somehow
wronged you, years ago.

01:55.542 --> 01:57.834
And now you're going to try
to even the score.

01:57.875 --> 02:00.250
-You can make anything
sound like it's annoying

02:00.291 --> 02:02.125
when you say it that way.

02:02.166 --> 02:04.375
-It's just, it's always your
story. Gerry's story this...

02:04.417 --> 02:06.875
What about my stories, right?
I got stories.

02:06.917 --> 02:09.083
-Okay, what story do you have
that you want to tell?

02:09.125 --> 02:11.333
-I don't have a good one
right now. I...

02:11.375 --> 02:13.667
I didn't know we were going
to do story time...So...

02:13.709 --> 02:15.834
-You don't have one.

02:15.875 --> 02:18.291
Let me tell you my story about
Donovan Bailey, it's a good
story.

02:18.333 --> 02:20.709
-Fine Gerry, what did
Donovan Bailey do?

02:20.750 --> 02:22.667
[♪ 80's Music]
-Back in high school...

02:22.709 --> 02:26.250
My senior year. Donovan
transferred for his last year,
from another school.

02:26.291 --> 02:31.000
Now, I don't know if you knew
this, in high school I was
captain of the track team.

02:31.041 --> 02:35.041
Then he showed up and
next thing you know...

02:35.083 --> 02:38.208
♪ 80's Music

02:38.250 --> 02:40.500
♪ 80's Music

02:40.542 --> 02:43.417
-Hey, not sure you're
supposed to be here...

02:43.458 --> 02:45.792
We have track and field
practice right now.

02:45.834 --> 02:48.291
-I know, Coach Simpson
invited me.

02:48.333 --> 02:53.041
-Well that's not possible.
Season's already started
and we got a full team here.

02:53.083 --> 02:55.417
-And who are you?

02:55.458 --> 02:57.333
-Who am I?

02:57.375 --> 02:59.709
I'm Gerry Duncan, the fastest
man in the school.

02:59.750 --> 03:03.333
-Oh really? Gerry Duncan,
why don't we race for it?

03:03.375 --> 03:07.291
One hundred meter straight.
If you beat me, I walk away.

03:07.333 --> 03:09.375
-Oh.
-How about it?

03:09.417 --> 03:11.583
-Wow. Wow!

03:11.625 --> 03:13.834
You wanna embarrass yourself
in front of everybody?

03:13.875 --> 03:16.458
-Bring it on.
-Boy, you're serious, aren't ya?

03:16.500 --> 03:19.041
-Yeah, yeah!
-Let's do this.

03:19.083 --> 03:21.291
-Let's go.

03:21.333 --> 03:23.875
[Donovan Bailey chuckles]

03:25.291 --> 03:27.458
-Alright.
-Ooh, whoo, whoo!

03:27.500 --> 03:31.291
[♪ Music stops, watch beeps]
-One sec. I still don't know
how to get it off alarm.

03:31.333 --> 03:34.333
Ach.
-[Donovan sighs]

03:34.375 --> 03:36.417
♪ 80's Music

03:36.458 --> 03:38.875
-Okay.

03:38.917 --> 03:41.208
-Ready?

03:41.250 --> 03:43.709
♪ 80's Music

03:43.750 --> 03:46.125
[Donovan chuckles]
[♪ 80's Music]

03:46.166 --> 03:48.458
One...two...
-Three...Go!

03:48.500 --> 03:51.041
[♪ 80's Music]

03:51.083 --> 03:53.834
[♪ 80's Music]
-Hey! Hammy, ugh.

03:53.875 --> 03:57.041
Ahh! Hammy.
Oh God, pulled it good.

03:57.083 --> 03:59.375
No race, right off.
Hamstring gone.

03:59.417 --> 04:01.667
Pulled it right off.
Oh gosh. Oh!

04:01.709 --> 04:05.834
-Guess who the new fastest
man in the school is, Gerry.

04:05.875 --> 04:07.875
-What?

04:07.917 --> 04:11.291
-My olympic dreams are crushed.
I guess I'll be a teacher.

04:11.333 --> 04:13.625
-[Bill]: You didn't say that.
-The race didn't count.

04:13.667 --> 04:15.917
It was a pointless race because
I pulled my hamstring.

04:15.959 --> 04:19.375
-Right.
-He went on, made the
national team, shoulda been me.

04:19.417 --> 04:21.625
Shoulda been me on the
national team.

04:21.667 --> 04:24.291
And then he went and became
a gold medalist in the Olympics.

04:24.333 --> 04:27.000
And I ended up...
-You became a middle aged
man with a roommate.

04:27.041 --> 04:31.000
-I became a teacher...
Is what I was gonna say.

04:31.041 --> 04:33.291
♪ Music

04:33.333 --> 04:35.250
-Heeeey.

04:35.291 --> 04:37.458
Who are you going to the
semi-formal with?

04:37.500 --> 04:39.625
-Oh, I'm going to drive myself.
You want a lift?

04:39.667 --> 04:41.625
-Ah, not who you driving
with, who ya goin' with?

04:41.667 --> 04:44.208
-Well, I'm not going with anyone
Simon, 'cause I'm supervising.

04:44.250 --> 04:46.667
I'm gonna pry the kids apart
when they start climbing
each other.

04:46.709 --> 04:49.125
-Ugh.
I'm gonna ask Nisha to the semi.

04:49.166 --> 04:51.709
-No, teachers don't bring dates.
That's what your semi-formal was
for.

04:51.750 --> 04:56.417
-I didn't make it to mine.
Shyness induced shingles
took care of that.

04:56.458 --> 04:58.917
Oh my gosh, there she is.

04:58.959 --> 05:01.375
Oh, oh...I'm a little nervous.
Are you nervous?

05:01.417 --> 05:03.583
-No.
-Of course you're not nervous.
You don't have a date

05:03.625 --> 05:06.709
You're just gonna stand on
the side of the gym with all
the other frumpy dumps.

05:06.750 --> 05:08.834
-Pump the brakes there, buddy.
-But not me.

05:08.875 --> 05:11.792
This year I'm going to slow
dance with somebody I'm
not related to.

05:11.834 --> 05:15.291
This year, I will have a semi.

05:15.333 --> 05:18.333
-Hey guys!
-Hey...

05:18.375 --> 05:22.000
My gosh she's intimidating.
-Unbelievable.

05:22.041 --> 05:24.250
-None of your business why
I need the number.

05:24.291 --> 05:26.500
Why don't you just give me
his number?

05:26.542 --> 05:28.500
-Awww, what's the matter Gerry?

05:28.542 --> 05:31.000
-No, I'm just trying to figure
out a way to reach someone.

05:31.041 --> 05:33.125
-Have you tried calling them?

05:33.166 --> 05:35.458
-[Mocking Voice]: Yes,
I've tried calling them.

05:35.500 --> 05:38.208
The person I'm calling won't
give me his number.

05:38.250 --> 05:41.208
-Who is it that you're
trying to reach?

05:41.250 --> 05:43.208
-Donovan Bailey.

05:43.250 --> 05:46.000
-Olympic gold medalist and
former fastest man in the
world Donovan Bailey?

05:46.041 --> 05:48.208
-I don't know what he did
with his life.

05:48.250 --> 05:50.792
-Whoo, I wouldn't mind reaching
Donovan Bailey.

05:50.834 --> 05:53.000
[Laughs and growls]

05:53.041 --> 05:55.417
-Huge help as always,
thanks Emma.

05:55.458 --> 05:57.417
-Look, Gerry...

05:57.458 --> 06:00.583
If you want to contact
a celebrity, it's simple.

06:00.625 --> 06:03.417
Two words.
Viral...

06:03.458 --> 06:06.625
-Uh...I know where you're going.
I know what you and Ted are up
to.

06:06.667 --> 06:09.375
And that's disgusting.
-Viral video Gerry!

06:09.417 --> 06:12.458
And for your information we both
have a clean bill of health.

06:12.500 --> 06:14.333
-Okay.
-Whatcha do...

06:14.375 --> 06:16.625
Is you get one of the students
to ask him to the semi formal.

06:16.667 --> 06:20.041
Then, you post it online
and you lure him in.

06:20.083 --> 06:22.500
-I've seen people do that, but
you really think that works?

06:22.542 --> 06:25.417
-Ah, it does work.
Like, all the time.

06:25.458 --> 06:27.625
-When's the semi formal?
-Friday.

06:27.667 --> 06:29.583
You should use Victoria as bait.

06:29.625 --> 06:32.500
She's got her own YouTube
channel. She has lots of
followers.

06:32.542 --> 06:34.875
You'll get tons of hits.
-Thank you Emma.

06:34.917 --> 06:37.125
That is good advice.

06:37.959 --> 06:40.417
Why are you giving me
good advice?

06:40.458 --> 06:42.709
-Because Gerry...

06:42.750 --> 06:46.458
I feel sorry for you.
You're a sad little man.

06:46.500 --> 06:49.083
[Laughs]
-Alright.

06:49.125 --> 06:52.291
-Done.
-This is quite a system
we got going on here.

06:52.333 --> 06:54.250
-Yeah.
-[Lisa chuckles]

06:54.291 --> 06:56.417
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

06:56.458 --> 06:59.458
-Ah, yearbooks. Printed
posterity in a digital age.
Weird.

06:59.500 --> 07:03.834
Look at you Miss Mason, putting
your little stamp on everything.
[Hisses]

07:03.875 --> 07:06.291
Would you like my
John Hancock on those?

07:06.333 --> 07:09.625
-[Both]: No thank you.
-No? Great.

07:09.667 --> 07:13.333
-[Lisa]: Hello.
-[Trudy]: Hi. Thank you.

07:13.375 --> 07:16.417
-Trudy, do you have a
pen I can borrow?
-No, just this one.

07:16.458 --> 07:18.709
-Lisa?
-Sorry.

07:18.750 --> 07:21.875
-No problem...Um...

07:23.333 --> 07:25.291
-[Trudy]: There you go.

07:27.041 --> 07:29.375
-They didn't want to wait?
-Ahh, no.

07:29.417 --> 07:31.291
-Cool.
-[Trudy]: Does anybody?

07:31.333 --> 07:33.500
-This yearbook signing business
is getting out of control.

07:33.542 --> 07:36.333
My hand hasn't been this cramped
since my honeymoon.

07:36.375 --> 07:38.333
[Emma and Trudy laugh]

07:38.375 --> 07:40.625
[Trudy]: The trick, of course,
is to alternate hands.

07:40.667 --> 07:44.166
-Ahhh.
-[Robert meow's]

07:45.375 --> 07:48.125
-Victoria! Hey!
-Oh, hey Mr. D. What's up?

07:48.166 --> 07:50.250
-Listen, do you have a date
to the semi formal?

07:50.291 --> 07:53.125
-Sir, I don't think teachers
can take students.

07:53.166 --> 07:55.333
-Very funny. Not what I meant.

07:55.375 --> 07:58.333
-Well, I'm going with my
boyfriend.
-Big mistake. Big mistake.

07:58.375 --> 08:01.333
Look, Nelson's a good guy,
but you're in the prime of
your life.

08:01.375 --> 08:04.250
You could take anyone in the
whole world. Why would you
take Nelson?

08:04.291 --> 08:07.458
-I suppose that's true.
-So, let's reach for the stars.

08:07.500 --> 08:11.041
Let's do one of those viral
videos that you specialize in.

08:11.083 --> 08:13.250
Let's do one of those celebrity
crush invites.

08:13.291 --> 08:17.583
-Oh! I'm in.
Oh! Josh Groban!

08:17.625 --> 08:20.709
-Oh! Donovan Bailey.

08:20.750 --> 08:23.000
-Who?
-Josh Groverman.

08:23.041 --> 08:25.125
-Oh my god, I'm so excited.

08:25.166 --> 08:27.417
-Meet me in my room after
school, we'll shoot this thing.

08:27.458 --> 08:30.125
-Okay!
-Okay. Hey Nelson.

08:30.166 --> 08:32.417
♪ Music

08:32.458 --> 08:36.000
-Suzie, Sarah, that's enough
talking. Get to class you two.
Okay?

08:36.041 --> 08:39.041
-Guess who!
-[Gasps]: Uncle Tommy?
How did you find me?

08:39.083 --> 08:41.417
-Oh, no, no, no.
It's me, don't worry.

08:41.458 --> 08:45.000
-Oh, Mr. Hunt! Oh thank heavens.
Ah, what's up?

08:45.041 --> 08:48.917
-Ah, you can call me Simon.
-Alright.

08:48.959 --> 08:52.667
Sssiimon.
[Nisha laughs]

08:52.709 --> 08:54.875
Sounds fun...
-Okay, okay.

08:54.917 --> 08:57.458
So. There's this, like um,
semi formal...

08:57.500 --> 09:00.875
Ah dance thing coming up that
I don't know if you've heard
about it.

09:00.917 --> 09:03.125
You probably don't even
want to go.

09:03.166 --> 09:05.291
-I'd love to go!
-Really?

09:05.333 --> 09:08.417
-Of course. It's just...
Nobody asked me.

09:08.458 --> 09:12.709
-Oh actually, Robert did ask
you to supervise. Remember that?

09:12.750 --> 09:15.291
-Always a bridesmaid, I guess.

09:16.333 --> 09:18.375
-Well, Ms. Nisha...

09:18.417 --> 09:22.917
Would you do me the honour
of accompanying me to the
Xavier Academy semi formal?

09:22.959 --> 09:25.458
-Oh, Simon! Yes.
-Really?

09:25.500 --> 09:27.417
-A thousand times yes!

09:27.458 --> 09:29.583
-There's just one thing...
It's my mother.

09:29.625 --> 09:33.041
Would you be able to come over
before the dance, just to meet
her really quick?

09:33.083 --> 09:36.458
-Um, could I? How else
would we get her blessing?

09:36.500 --> 09:38.667
Hello?
-Good point.

09:38.709 --> 09:41.375
-[Nisha laughs]: Right?
-Bobbi.

09:41.417 --> 09:43.834
-Ahhhh.

09:43.875 --> 09:47.250
Can you believe it?
-[Bobbi]: No.

09:47.291 --> 09:48.542
♪ Music

09:50.333 --> 09:52.667
-Need you to do it again.
Need you to stick to the script.

09:52.709 --> 09:54.750
-[Victoria]: Okay. Whoo.

09:54.792 --> 09:58.458
You'll always be the gold medal
winner of my heart, and if you
could be my date for the

09:58.500 --> 10:00.792
for the semi formal, Mr. Groban,
I would do anything...

10:00.834 --> 10:04.041
-Cut, cut, cut. I said we can't
use names, you can't use names.

10:04.083 --> 10:06.250
What if Josh Groban can't do
this?

10:06.291 --> 10:09.458
We've gotta substitute the
footage in with some...

10:09.500 --> 10:11.917
Take five, I gotta figure this
out.

10:11.959 --> 10:15.625
-Oh, hey Frank.
-Josh Groban?

10:15.667 --> 10:17.625
-What?

10:19.458 --> 10:24.208
-Or is this the old viral video
semi formal celebrity invite
switcheroo?

10:26.375 --> 10:28.583
-How do you know that?
-Not my first rodeo, Gerry.

10:28.625 --> 10:30.500
Who's the real mark?

10:30.542 --> 10:34.208
-Donovan Bailey.
-[Inhales]: Canadian legend
Donovan Bailey?

10:34.250 --> 10:36.417
-He's not a legend.
-What do you want with him?

10:36.458 --> 10:38.333
-I have to race him.
-Oh man, I am so in.

10:38.375 --> 10:41.792
I love sprinters. You know as a
young boy I dreamed of running
in the olympics.

10:41.834 --> 10:44.834
Then of course, the good lord
took my legs in a tragic
accident so...

10:44.875 --> 10:47.375
-Okay, you know what? It's not
about your story it's about my
story.

10:47.417 --> 10:49.709
-Take it from me, you're not
gonna get Bailey with her.

10:49.750 --> 10:52.125
-Why?
-'Cause there's nothing
wrong with her.

10:52.166 --> 10:54.333
You need someone the internet
can rally around.

10:54.375 --> 10:56.291
-A kid asking, isn't that
enough?

10:56.333 --> 11:00.000
-Gerry, the world doesn't send
healthy kids to swim with the
dolphins.

11:00.041 --> 11:03.625
-I don't get what you mean.
-You need someone with
like, a facial deformity.

11:03.667 --> 11:05.583
Or like, a breathing problem.

11:05.625 --> 11:08.083
[Pretends he has
breathing problem]:
Come to my semi formal.

11:08.125 --> 11:10.417
-Oh.
-Yeah.

11:10.458 --> 11:12.875
-You're gonna be re-cast, sorry.
[♪ Music]

11:12.917 --> 11:15.333
-[Mouths]: Thank you.

11:15.458 --> 11:19.125
♪ Music

11:20.875 --> 11:23.166
[Nisha takes a deep breath]

11:26.417 --> 11:29.834
-Mrs. Hunt, it is so nice to
finally meet you.

11:29.875 --> 11:32.000
I brought a pie.

11:32.041 --> 11:34.208
-[Both laugh]

11:35.542 --> 11:38.417
-[Simon]: Hey.
-[Mrs. Hunt]: Absolutely not!

11:38.458 --> 11:40.417
-[Simon]: Why not?
-[Mrs. Hunt]: She's a whore!

11:40.458 --> 11:43.375
[Mrs. Hunt]: All up in my face
with a pie.

11:43.417 --> 11:47.625
-[Simon]: That whore is an angel
and that angel-whore is my
semi formal date.

11:47.667 --> 11:50.834
-[Mrs. Hunt]: She's not coming
in here. I will not have it.

11:50.875 --> 11:55.000
That meatloaf is not going
down that sluts throat,
I'll tell you that right now.

11:55.041 --> 11:58.250
-[Simon]: You're smothering me.
-[Mrs. Hunt]: Don't think I
haven't thought about it.

11:58.291 --> 12:00.625
[Simon]: Are you threatening
me now?
-[Mrs. Hunt]: I'm gonna...

12:00.667 --> 12:03.667
[Simon]: Are you threatening
me now?
-[Mrs. Hunt]: Stop it...No...No!

12:03.709 --> 12:06.083
Nooo!
-[Simon]: Hey, hey.

12:06.125 --> 12:09.291
-Hey.
-Oh a pie, that looks good.

12:09.333 --> 12:12.458
Listen, we're just gonna...
Dinner's just going to be
a few more minutes.

12:12.500 --> 12:17.417
[Door slams]
[Simon and Mrs. Hunt scream]

12:17.458 --> 12:20.166
♪ Music

12:21.542 --> 12:25.041
-Amy Biel. Severe dyslexia.
She's a mess.

12:25.083 --> 12:27.000
-That's it?
-Cool.

12:27.041 --> 12:30.709
-Olivia Morton. Low self-esteem.
-Every kid has that now-a-days,
Frank.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.917
-True.

12:32.959 --> 12:35.250
Kelly Mendelson.
Cancer survivor.

12:35.291 --> 12:38.291
-Cancer survivor? But then
she's cured, what's the point?

12:38.333 --> 12:40.250
-Yeah, only for three years
though.

12:40.291 --> 12:42.417
She's not officially out of the
woods until year five.

12:42.458 --> 12:46.625
-So, she's cured...But
technically it could come back.

12:46.667 --> 12:50.709
If Donovan Bailey doesn't come
for this girl, he's a monster.

12:50.750 --> 12:54.000
-And, I just love you so much,
it would change my life forever

12:54.041 --> 12:58.000
if you'd come to Xavier and be
my date to the semi formal.

12:58.041 --> 13:00.375
Thank you!
How was that?

13:00.417 --> 13:03.709
-Ah, that was good, Kelly.
But you really want Drake
to come, right?

13:03.750 --> 13:07.125
-So much.
-We've got a few pointers
to help with that.

13:07.166 --> 13:10.291
Kelly, the elephant in the
room is, you're a cancer
survivor right?

13:10.333 --> 13:14.000
-Yeah?
-Congratulations, on that,
by the way.

13:14.041 --> 13:16.208
But we need more of that
into the camera.

13:16.250 --> 13:18.333
Like, what type of
cancer was it?

13:18.375 --> 13:21.291
-Ah, Basal Cell Carcinoma.
-Ugh. Gross.

13:21.333 --> 13:23.583
That sounds gross.
Well, talk about it.

13:23.625 --> 13:27.500
What chemo therapy was like.
-Oh no, I was in and out.

13:27.542 --> 13:30.792
-Of consciousness, of course.
-Yeah, talk about being
unconscious.

13:30.834 --> 13:33.625
-No, no. Like I was in and
out of the hospital.

13:33.667 --> 13:36.458
The doctor just removed the
mole and I was cured.

13:36.500 --> 13:38.375
-This is a disaster.

13:38.417 --> 13:40.583
-One sec.
[Quietly]: I have an idea, stick
with me here.

13:40.625 --> 13:45.291
-Kelly, we're going to take
this viral video in a little
bit of a different direction.

13:45.333 --> 13:50.041
-Okay, sure.
-Okay, just read that into
the camera, okay?

13:50.083 --> 13:53.458
We're going to get him.
-Oh, actually let's start with
a few lip trills.

13:53.500 --> 13:57.333
[Frank and Kelly make
noises with lips]

13:57.375 --> 14:00.625
-And repeat after me.
Donovan Bailey.

14:00.667 --> 14:03.333
-Donovan Bailey.
-Perfect.

14:05.417 --> 14:08.208
-Oh, Mr. Cheeley?
-Mmm hmm, that's me.

14:08.250 --> 14:11.500
The man...The myth...The...
What's up?

14:11.542 --> 14:15.458
-I need something signed.
-Lucy, I'd be happy to.

14:15.500 --> 14:17.625
-I need a sign out slip,
I don't feel well.

14:19.458 --> 14:22.208
-That's it?
-I really don't feel well?

14:22.250 --> 14:24.667
Can I see your yearbook
for a second?

14:24.709 --> 14:27.000
-Oh, how's this?

14:27.041 --> 14:27.917
-That is perfect.

14:30.083 --> 14:34.417
And if you need anything else
signed, anything else
whatsoever, you let me know.

14:34.458 --> 14:36.583
-Thanks Mr. Cheeley.
-Thank you.

14:36.625 --> 14:39.000
-Oh, Mr. Malik, will you
sign my yearbook?

14:39.041 --> 14:41.291
-Certainly.

14:43.333 --> 14:45.500
-That's my pen.
-Here you go.

14:45.542 --> 14:47.875
[♪ Music]
-Thanks. I love that.

14:49.417 --> 14:52.208
-Donovan Bailey.
I am love you.

14:52.250 --> 14:54.625
I am riddled with cancer.

14:54.667 --> 14:58.041
I only have a few days left
to ask you this question.

14:58.083 --> 15:02.250
Please be my date to the
semi formal this Friday at
Xavier Academy.

15:02.291 --> 15:04.875
If you can't make it,
I'll probably die.

15:04.917 --> 15:07.417
I love you.
Donovan Bailey.

15:07.458 --> 15:09.625
-I think that worked.

15:09.667 --> 15:12.458
[Gerry's running cleats
click clack on the floor]

15:12.500 --> 15:15.917
[Gerry's running cleats
click clack on the floor]

15:15.959 --> 15:17.792
-Sir, what did you do?

15:17.834 --> 15:20.875
-What? That video went viral.
You should be thanking me.

15:20.917 --> 15:24.709
-You made the video all
weird and you didn't use
anything that I actually said.

15:24.750 --> 15:27.667
And I still don't know
who Donovan Bailey is?

15:27.709 --> 15:30.250
-I used...
-Five time world Olympic
champion.

15:30.291 --> 15:33.417
-Who the hell are you?
-Your semi-formal date, Kelly.

15:33.458 --> 15:37.250
-You're not Drake!
What's going on Mr. Duncan?

15:37.291 --> 15:40.875
-Duncan?
[Donovan Bailey laughs]

15:40.917 --> 15:43.291
-Gerry Duncan?
-Hello, Donovan.

15:43.333 --> 15:47.917
-Wow! You did all of this,
just to get me here?

15:47.959 --> 15:49.875
-And it worked.

15:49.917 --> 15:52.709
So, how about you and
me have a little rematch,
unless you're afraid.

15:52.750 --> 15:54.834
-Afraid?

15:56.667 --> 16:00.333
Donovan Bailey's always
ready to run. Let's go.

16:00.375 --> 16:02.417
-Okay, that's just ridiculous.

16:07.959 --> 16:11.125
[Gerry's running cleats
click clack on the floor]

16:11.166 --> 16:14.542
[♪ Music]
[Gerry's running cleats
scrape on the floor]

16:15.125 --> 16:17.417
[♪ Music]
-[Gerry]: Okay, whoo, whoo,
whoo.

16:17.458 --> 16:19.709
Okay, had to switch my shoes.
Now I'm ready.

16:19.750 --> 16:22.667
-Okay Gerry, one hundred meters
to that tree right there.

16:22.709 --> 16:25.083
-Okay, that's way more than
a hundred meters.

16:27.709 --> 16:30.000
-One hundred exactly.

16:30.041 --> 16:32.000
-Okay.

